VERDICT: APPROVED_WITH_COMMENTS
The changes are functionally correct for the stated scope (faster owner-hit panic reaction, safer panic movement to avoid falls, and creator-response behavior), with only minor non-blocking issues.

Critical findings / analysis:
- Owner-hit reaction speed is improved: panic state is set immediately on attributed owner hit, active movement/combat controls are cleared right away, and panic timing is reset so movement starts on the next logic cycle without lag.
- Panic fall prevention is materially improved: panic now checks current ground safety before movement, uses directional safety checks with longer runway requirements, and in the latest working-tree update keeps sneak enabled and sprint disabled during panic movement to reduce edge-fall risk.
- Creator response is implemented reliably: both an explicit chat-path matcher and prompt-level instruction ensure deterministic replies to creator-origin questions, including Hinglish variants.

Security: none observed.

Next actions:
1) Clean up panic movement internals: `canSprint`/sprint runway logic is now effectively unused because sprint is always forced off; either remove the dead branch or re-enable sprint conditionally with clear intent.
2) Consider narrowing creator-question matching or adding lightweight throttling to avoid non-owner chat spam/false positives in busy public chat.
3) If this is the final submission, ensure the currently uncommitted files are intentionally included in the task completion diff to avoid partial delivery.

